 install <strong>wall lights<\/strong> on their own. The answer is, yes, you can! With a little DIY know-how, installing <strong>wall mounted lamps<\/strong> can be a straightforward task. You’ll typically need a drill, screws, a screwdriver, and some basic electrical knowledge if you're wiring the light to your home’s electrical system.<\/p><p>Here’s a simple guide to installing <strong>wall lamps for bedroom<\/strong> or any other room:<\/p><ol><li><strong>Choose the Right Location:<\/strong> Consider where you need light and how high you want the light to be positioned.<\/li><li><strong>Mark the Spot:<\/strong> Use a pencil to mark the spots for screws or mounting brackets.<\/li><li><strong>Drill Holes:<\/strong> Carefully drill the holes, making sure to avoid any hidden electrical wires within the wall.<\/li><li><strong>Mount the Fixture:<\/strong> Install the <strong>wall light<\/strong> fixture, ensuring it’s secure.<\/li><li><strong>Wire It Up:<\/strong> If the fixture needs to be wired, carefully connect the wires (or hire an electrician for safety).<\/li><\/ol><p>However, if you’re not comfortable with wiring, it’s always best to hire a professional to avoid any electrical risks. Fortunately, some <strong>wall mounted lights<\/strong> are plug-in, which makes installation easier without the need for wiring.<\/p>","txt_color":"","txt_fs":16,"txt_fw":400,"txt_tf":"unset","txt_mt":0,"txt_mb":25}}},"block_order":["heading_eeNPHN","text_DG8w8z"],"settings":{"container":"container","background_color":"","banner_type":"video","image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/s-l960_5_95e12f51-d328-4912-827f-05bb9e6c8bf5.webp","video_options":"local","video_local":"shopify:\/\/files\/videos\/0805 (2)_1 (1).mp4","video_url":"","link":"https:\/\/ledsone.co.uk\/collections\/wall-light","hover_effect":"zoom","bn_design":"text_column","banner_height":"depend-image","height_dk":800,"height_tb":600,"height_mb":360,"content_box":"content_in_container","text_bellow_mobile":false,"img_posit